            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I also do the same thing. I would only add that some people keep their initial `vim.lsp.config()` calls in lazy-loaded places (ftplugins and such). Which would mean that we could avoid iterating through active clients if before the call `vim.lsp.config[\"foo\"] = nil`?\n\nOther than that, I couldn't come up with a use case where a person would want to change settings without informing the server. Unless the server doesn't support that and requires restart. In which case, if this enhancement makes a promise to update the server-side config automagically, it should at least inform the user, since forcing restart would be bad.\n\nOr it could be a still explicit but more ergonomic `vim.lsp.update_config_smiley_face()`.",
