            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The 3 lines to trigger the update seems trivial/ergonomic enough?\n\nCurrently `lsp.config(server, new_config)` is primarily a means to set the configuration template for _future_ client/server instances. Not a means to update existing running client instances. If `lsp.config(name, conf)` would also update running instances we'd reduce flexibility by taking away the option to change the config _only_ for future instances.\n\nCould consider having `client.setting` changes auto-emit a didChangeConfiguration notification, but this kind of automation can also be confusing, and again - saving only a single line, so likely not worth doing.",
